Description: Body sherd of East Greek grey ware pottery closed vessel, possibly an oinochoe or dinos; dark grey fabric core sandwiched between dark reddish inner margins and brown outer margins, with numerous mica inclusions; dark grey slip and inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: Incised inscription on interior "Diosk" signifies findspot
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.098)
